  "title": "Function constructor injection in CustomMCP via mcpServerConfig",
  "description": "The convertToValidJSONString function in CustomMCP.ts calls Function('return ' + inputString)() where inputString originates from the user-controlled mcpServerConfig parameter. Because Function() compiles and executes arbitrary JavaScript with full Node.js runtime privileges, an attacker can inject payloads that invoke child_process.execSync or access the filesystem, achieving remote code execution on the Flowise server.",
